07/07/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- A homemade bomb exploded Monday (July 6th) outside a tax office in the Athens suburb of Galatsi, local media reported.
It heavily damaged the building's ground floor and two adjacent shops.
No injuries were reported.
This is the latest of a series of bombings in and near the capital in the past few days.
(ANA-MPA, Kathimerini, Vima - 06/07/09)
